Interface ModelInfo

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ModelGenerator, ModelGeneratorSymbolic
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultModelGenerator, ModulesFile, ModulesFileModelGenerator, ModulesFileModelGeneratorSymbolic, ProductModelGenerator, ProductModelGenerator2, TestModelGenerator

    public interface ModelInfo
    Interface for classes that provide some basic (syntactic) information about a probabilistic model.

    • Method Detail

      • getModelType

        ModelType getModelType()
        Get the type of probabilistic model.

      • setSomeUndefinedConstants

        default void setSomeUndefinedConstants(Values someValues)
                                throws PrismException
        Set values for *some* undefined constants. If there are no undefined constants, someValues can be null. Undefined constants can be subsequently redefined to different values with the same method. The current constant values (if set) are available via getConstantValues().
        Constant values are evaluated using standard (integer, floating-point) arithmetic.
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • setSomeUndefinedConstants

        default void setSomeUndefinedConstants(Values someValues,
                                       boolean exact)
                                throws PrismException
        Set values for *some* undefined constants. If there are no undefined constants, someValues can be null. Undefined constants can be subsequently redefined to different values with the same method. The current constant values (if set) are available via getConstantValues().
        Constant values are evaluated using either using standard (integer, floating-point) arithmetic or exact arithmetic, depending on the value of the exact flag.
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • getConstantValues

        default Values getConstantValues()
        Get access to the values for all constants in the model, including the undefined constants set previously via the method #setUndefinedConstants(Values). Until they are set for the first time, this method returns null.

      • getRewardStructIndex

        default int getRewardStructIndex(java.lang.String name)
        Get the index of a module by its name (indexed from 0, not from 1 like at the user (property language) level). Returns -1 if name does not exist.

      • getRewardStruct

        default RewardStruct getRewardStruct(int i)
        Get a reward structure by its index (indexed from 0, not from 1 like at the user (property language) level). Returns null if index is out of range.

      • rewardStructHasTransitionRewards

        default boolean rewardStructHasTransitionRewards(int i)
        Returns true if the reward structure with index i defines transition rewards. (indexed from 0, not from 1 like at the user (property language) level) If this returns false, the model checker is allowed to ignore them (which may be more efficient). If using an algorithm or implementation that does not support transition rewards, you may need to return false here (as well as not defining transition rewards).
